Subject: [PATCH AP-13] vmmon/vmnet: ensure -DVMMON / -DVMNET identity flags in Makefile.kernel

Some VMware source tarballs (particularly third-party rebuilds or community
overlays) omit the CC_OPTS += -DVMMON or -DVMNET line from Makefile.kernel.
These defines are the module's own identity flags — they guard code sections
that should only compile for one specific module (vmmon vs vmnet).

Without -DVMMON, vmmon may compile code paths intended only for vmnet, and
vice versa. The modules may compile but behave incorrectly at runtime, or
fail to compile due to missing symbols from the wrong module's namespace.

The community 6.16.x overlay's vmmon/Makefile.kernel already has
CC_OPTS += -DVMMON -DVMCORE on line 21. However, the vmnet overlay's
Makefile.kernel does not have -DVMNET. This patch documents the fix for
both modules.

Applied by: _autopatch_module_define() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  Always applied when -DVMMON or -DVMNET is absent from Makefile.kernel

---
 vmmon-only/Makefile.kernel | 3 +++   (if -DVMMON missing)
 vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel | 3 +++   (if -DVMNET missing)

Note: The vmmon overlay already has CC_OPTS += -DVMMON -DVMCORE.
The patch below shows the vmnet case (most commonly needed).

diff --git a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
--- a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
+++ b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
@@ -20,6 +20,9 @@ INCLUDE := -I$(SRCROOT)
 
 ccflags-y := $(CC_OPTS) $(INCLUDE)
+
+# Module identity define
+CC_OPTS += -DVMNET
